<subSubSection id="CFA9BED16C0CFFADFF43F98366283CE5" box="[197,1030,1649,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="870CED5A6C0CFFADFF43F98366283CE5" blockId="2.[151,1437,1577,2033]" box="[197,1030,1649,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis id="B5C731486C0CFFADFF43F98363623CE6" bold="true" box="[197,332,1650,1674]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Etymology.</emphasis>
This name is related to the yellow margin of the metapleuron.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFA9BED16C0CFFADFF43F96463A03D9D" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph id="870CED5A6C0CFFADFF43F96460833D51" blockId="2.[151,1437,1577,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
Small size. Body castaneous, veins of hemelytra concolorous except radial vein pale yellow. Scutellar spots small. Hemelytra without dark spots. Medial ridge of the mesosternum black. Calloused area of metapleuron yellow. Abdomen ventrally dark castaneous, sparsely punctured. Spiracles near a tumid concolorous area. Medial retrorsely produced process of seventh abdominal segment narrow, long, flat, arising from apical margin, this even, and apex expanded and slightly curved (
<figureCitation id="1F88F1DF6C0CFFADFDDCF8D460B13D51" box="[602,671,1829,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[211,1389,249,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–7. Callostethus flavolineatus sp. nov. 5–7, male; 5–6, pygophore; 5—dorsal view; 6—ventral view; 7—medial process of the seventh abdominal segment. (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204642/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number id="317BFF7D6C0CFFADFD09F8D460B13D51" box="[655,671,1829,1853]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="870CED5A6C0CFFADFF43F8B867443DA1" blockId="2.[151,1437,1577,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
Male (
<figureCitation id="1F88F1DF6C0CFFADFE8BF8B863543D0D" box="[269,378,1865,1889]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1242,1265]" captionTargetBox="[211,1389,249,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1221]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 5–7. Callostethus flavolineatus sp. nov. 5–7, male; 5–6, pygophore; 5—dorsal view; 6—ventral view; 7—medial process of the seventh abdominal segment. (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204642/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">
Figs. 
<number id="317BFF7D6C0CFFADFECAF8B863543D0D" box="[332,378,1865,1889]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim projected medially. Posterolateral angle flattish and rectangular in lateral view. Ventral rim narrow and fold dorsally; area of contact with posterolateral angles not membranous. Paramere uncinate with distal part wide, flat, rounded; near its base arises a small digitiform process pointed anteriorly. Proctiger with dorsal processes short, dorsally directed; posterior face sloped with lateral margin tumid.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="870CED5A6C0CFFADFF43F82863A03D9D" blockId="2.[151,1437,1577,2033]" box="[197,398,2009,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="57">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CFA9BED16C0DFFACFF43FF6666503A94" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="870CED5A6C0DFFACFF43FF6666503A94" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B5C731486C0DFFACFF43FF6663633ADC" bold="true" box="[197,333,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Comments.</emphasis>
This specimen is smaller and darker than 
<taxonomicName id="40B396D96C0DFFACFCB5FF69663F3ADC" box="[819,1041,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Callostethus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatopunctatus">
<emphasis id="B5C731486C0DFFACFCB5FF69663F3ADC" box="[819,1041,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">C. guttatopunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="1F88F1DF6C0DFFACFBA4FF6666493AC3" box="[1058,1127,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1976,1999]" captionTargetBox="[462,1122,1376,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[391,1189,1345,1932]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 8–9. dorsal view of the species of Callostethus. 8—C. flavolineatus sp. nov., 9—C. guttatopunctatus (Fabricius, 1803)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204643/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Fig. 
<number id="317BFF7D6C0DFFACFBDEFF6666493AC3" box="[1112,1127,151,175]" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
). Other diagnostic features are the small yellow marks on scutellum, the medial ridge of the mesosternum black, and the medial retrorsely produced process of the seventh abdominal segment arising from the margin of the segment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
